# Data access via server components and server actions

- **Reads only in server components**: All data retrieval from our database or external data layer must happen in server-only contexts:
  - Next.js server components (e.g. files under `app/` that are not marked `"use client"`)
  - Route handlers / API routes
  - Server utilities that are only ever called from the above

- **Writes only in server actions**: Any operation that **inserts**, **updates**, or **deletes** data in our database must be implemented as a **server action**, and only invoked from the client via that server action. Do **not** write directly from client components, hooks, or effects.

## Examples

- **Valid: read in a server component**

```ts
// app/dashboard/page.tsx (server component)
import { db } from "@/db";
import { items } from "@/db/schema";

export default async function DashboardPage() {
  const data = await db.select().from(items);

  return (
    <div>
      <h1>Dashboard</h1>
      {/* pass data down to client components as props if needed */}
    </div>
  );
}
```

- **Valid: write via a server action**

```ts
// app/items/actions.ts
"use server";

import { db } from "@/db";
import { items } from "@/db/schema";

export async function createItem(input: { name: string }) {
  await db.insert(items).values({ name: input.name });
}
```

```ts
// app/items/page.tsx (can be a client component using the action)
"use client";

import { useTransition } from "react";
import { createItem } from "./actions";

export function NewItemForm() {
  const [isPending, startTransition] = useTransition();

  return (
    <form
      action={async (formData: FormData) => {
        const name = formData.get("name") as string;
        startTransition(() => createItem({ name }));
      }}
    >
      <input name="name" />
      <button type="submit" disabled={isPending}>
        Create
      </button>
    </form>
  );
}
```

- **Invalid: writing directly from a client component (not allowed)**

```ts
// ❌ Do NOT do this
"use client";

import { db } from "@/db"; // or any direct data layer import

export function BadComponent() {
  async function handleClick() {
    // ❌ Direct write from client
    await db.insert(/* ... */);
  }

  return <button onClick={handleClick}>Save</button>;
}
```

Always move:

- **Reads** into server components / route handlers, and
- **Writes** into server actions that the client calls, never directly into the data layer from the client.

